  "body": "This is an alternative approach to https://github.com/facebook/react/pull/14153. This PR aims at clearing the memory leak when the associated fibers containing the references to the closures (stored in `memoizedState`) still exist after being unmounted. The fix is to simply `null` out the `memoizedState` field which seems to clear up the retained functions.",
